.SH NAME
aurl-add - Register an API as a CLI command


.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBaurl add [name] [spec or endpoint] [flags]\fP


.SH DESCRIPTION
Register an OpenAPI spec or GraphQL endpoint as a named CLI command.

.PP
Examples:
  aurl add petstore https://petstore.swagger.io/openapi.json
  aurl add --graphql countries https://countries.trevorblades.com/graphql


.SH OPTIONS
\fB--base-url\fP=""
	Override the base URL from the spec

.PP
\fB--graphql\fP[=false]
	Register a GraphQL endpoint instead of an OpenAPI spec

.PP
\fB--header\fP=[]
	Auth header (e.g., "Authorization: Bearer token")

.PP
\fB-h\fP, \fB--help\fP[=false]
	help for add


.SH SEE ALSO
\fBaurl(1)\fP


